>Magra: AEEHIJP 14K HAJI +33 391
#note I really screwed this one up but got lucky and didn't suffer the consequences of it. Fairly low on time by this juncture, I wasn't sure if I could beat him for sure if I tried to block at the top-right, because he would probably score too buch with his blank. I thought about HADJI but I don't always have an out afterwards. However the right play is definitely HADJEE at that same spot, playing through an extra tile. I really wish that had occurred to me, but instead I resorted to luck for victory.
>Mike_Baker: ?ADDERR K3 D.AD +22 372
#note this is a nice play, although evidently DEED is slightly better at the exact same spot.
>Magra: EEEP H1 PE.. +18 409
#note blocking his best out (which I didn't even realize at the time) as well as just scoring best
>Mike_Baker: ?ERR 6I R..ERs +6 378
#note I took a good long look at the pre-endgame and here's what I come up with. HADJEE does win all games because I always have an out. Sometimes Mike could set up an out-in-two while blocking my out but I still score enough to win. With my play of HAJI I lose if the A or an R is in the bag, to DODDERER or LADDERED/DAIKERED/DANDERED. Finally with HADJI it gets more complicated - I lose if I draw the A or the E, because in those situations I don't have an out, allowing Mike a big play on row 14, leading to me losing by 2 or 3 points. Some of those endgames might be stealable if he misses something though. I think he is more likely to see the bingos than to make the right play sequence to go out, which means I made the wrong move and should've played HADJI (disregarding that HADJEE is best of all had I seen it).
>Mike_Baker:  (EE) +4 382
#note Last tidbit, given the last tile in the bag (an E) I would've lost had I played HADJI instead of HAJI at the bottom-right.
